5 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REQUIRING THE DISPLAY OF THE TEN COMMANDMENTS
6 AND THE SEVEN PRINCIPLES OF UNITARIAN UNIVERSALISM IN EACH PUBLIC SCHOOL BUILDING
7 AND CLASSROOM; PROVIDING SPECIFICATIONS FOR THE TEXT AND THE DISPLAY OF THE TEN
8 COMMANDMENTS AND THE SEVEN PRINCIPLES OF UNITARIAN UNIVERSALISM; AUTHORIZING A
9 DISTRICT TO SPEND ITS OWN FUNDS OR DONATED FUNDS TO PROVIDE THE DISPLAYS OR TO
10 ACCEPT DONATED DISPLAYS ; EXCLUDING THE DISPLAY OF THE TEN COMMANDMENTS AND THE
11 SEVEN PRINCIPLES OF UNITARIAN UNIVERSALISM FROM THE PROHIBITION AGAINST DISTRIBUTION
12 OF SECTARIAN OR DENOMINATIONAL PUBLICATIONS IN A PUBLIC SCHOOL; AMENDING SECTION 20-
13 7-112, MCA; AND PROVIDING AN EFFECTIVE DATE.”
14
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
16
17 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Required display of ten commandments and seven principles of
18 unitarian universalism. (1) The trustees of a district shall display the ten commandments and the seven
19 principles of unitarian universalism in each school building and in each classroom of each school in the district.
20 (2) The ten commandments and the seven principles of unitarian universalism must each be
21 displayed on a poster or framed document that is a minimum size of 11 inches by 14 inches. The text of the ten
22 commandments and the seven principles of unitarian universalism must be the central focus of the poster or
23 framed document and must be printed in a large, easily readable font.
24 (3) The text of the ten commandments display must read as follows:
25 "THE TEN COMMANDMENTS
26 I AM the LORD thy God, thou shalt have no other gods before me.
27 Thou shalt not make to thyself any graven images.
