5 classroom as required by [section 1];
6 (ii)(iii) a pupil student from reading from the Bible or other religious material during free reading time;
7 or
8 (iii)(iv) a student from initiating or participating in a conversation about religion, religious beliefs, or
9 religious practices. with another student or a teacher.
10 (c) If a school, class, or course has requirements for self-selected reading, a pupil student must be
11 allowed to read from the Bible or other religious material to meet those requirements.
12 (2) Prayer is permitted in a school, on school grounds, and at school-sponsored events, but a
13 person may not be compelled to pray. The school day may begin with a prayer."
